The maximum income of the country is then

$8 \alpha * \alpha+1 *\left(100-4 \alpha^{2}\right)=4 \alpha^{2}+100$.

If the country's income with the change in the price of good X is greater than the expenses on the set of goods $X_{\text {cons }}=1.5, \quad Y_{\text {cons }}=92$, i.e., $4 \alpha^{2}+100>8 \alpha * 1.5+1 * 92$, then the country will benefit from an increase in the price of good X. The inequality will be satisfied for $\alpha>1$ only if $\alpha>2$, that is, if the price of good X increases by more than two times.

